Package edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.course

Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.course.Activity
      • edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.course.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Conflict
    public class Event
extends Activity
    Event class for WolfScheduler, use to create Event objects. An Event object consists of the title, weekly repeat, event details, meeting days, start time and end time. Extends the Activity class.
    Author:
    Sanjana Cheerla

        public void setMeetingDays​(java.lang.String meetingDays)
        Sets the Event's meetingDays. If the meetingDays contains any other characters than "M,T,W,H,F,S,U", an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. An IllegalArgumentException is also thrown if meetingDays is null or empty.
        Overrides:
        setMeetingDays in class Activity
        Parameters:
        meetingDays - The meetingDays to set
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If meetingDays is null or empty, and if the meetingDays are invalid meaning that it must have "M" "T" "W" "T" "F" "S" "U" as a combination of strings and no other characters.
